This port of the game is abysmal. Why was it so hard just to emulate an NES game. I understand that they wanted to remake it for the ground up optimised for smartphones but there's no excuse for the game to be released in this state. The frame-rate is -20 fps on normal mode which may not sound slow but for a game that needs twitch reflexes and pinpoint controls it's unplayable. Especially when the NES from 1983 can run it at a stable 60 fps. There's no excuse. Now, if you really want to play Mega Man on your phone, (which I don't recommend in the first place since in my opinion, you NEED a controller for these games) just get an NES emulator for your phone and just download the Mega Man ROMS. Sure, downloading ROMS legally is a grey area but by downloading this game you are supporting these low effort, unplayable, terrible ports. And to the people who say "This is perfect. This is exactly how it played on the NES." No. It's not. I can 100% guarantee you that Mega Man on the NES did not play this terribly.

Wow. Just wow. How can you mess up Mega Man this badly? I've seen better frame rates on the MS-DOS games. In fact, I'd rather play those than this garbage. The game lags severely, unlike on the original NES, which ran smoother, and that's saying alot. In fact, the lag can get so bad, that it is really difficult to time jumps correctly, and you end up falling to your death. I do give them credit for making a really cool and easy to use weapon select menu, but that doesn't fix the fact that this "port" is a pile of garbage. If you want to play a better version of this, I'd reccomend getting it on the Nintendo eshop.

content: It is MegaMan 1, just like on NES! Except, a lot of improvements have been made that are bound to make newer gamers comfortable. I'm a veteran MegaMan fan, and I have no problem going through the original game. And even to me this was pleasant.  I am not sure why they kept the framerate this low. It does look bad, just as bad as in the trailers. This is such a shame. Fixing THAT alone would have made it a lot better for basically everyone.  The controls, this might apply to all other MegaMan games, but they are not that clever. I wish there was a secondary shoot button on the left, allowing me to jump with the right thumb, and shoot comfortably with the left thumb. (for those moments you have to jump and shoot but not necessarily be moving)  Thanks Capcom! But please make updates. If there ever was a time an update was necessary, this would be it.
HAPPY 29TH MEGA MAN!
